reviewText: Presented by Alan Titchmarsh, contains a selection of some National Trust`s gardens.  The gardens are great and are amongst the most famous in England.  Although the shootage is just enough in quality and the whole work is not a breathtaking one. As I am not an English native speaker I miss subtitles too.  A good point is the close-ups in some particular plants with name of cultivars, etc.  It is interesting for my work as a landscaper.
